## What CASA Is Proposing (11 Items)

### Section 3.2 – Sub-250g drones near people *(no approval needed)*
Allow drones ≤250g to operate within 30m of people without CASA approval, provided the operator holds a RePL and certain criteria are met.

### Section 4.2 – Physical barrier separates drone from people *(no approval needed)*
Allow drones ≤25kg to operate over/near people where all people are reasonably protected by a structure or barrier, without CASA approval where criteria are met.

### Section 5.1 – CONOPS / application detail requirements *(process change)*
CASA would seek additional operational details via a submitted CONOPS or application questions, for pathways that require a CASA approval.

### Section 5.2 – OONP with other CASA approvals assessed together *(new requirement)*
OONP conducted in conjunction with other CASA approvals (outside standard operating conditions) must be applied for and assessed together.

### Section 5.3 – Major gatherings / organised events *(new requirement)*
Restrict OONP at major gatherings unless applied for and approved by CASA. Operator must hold a letter of agreement from the event organiser and notify CASA ≥7 days prior.

### Section 5.4 – Emergency Response Plan (ERP) *(new requirement)*
OONP approval holders must have an ERP commensurate with the complexity and risk of the operation.

### Section 5.5 – Pathway 1: Informed consenting active participants *(refinement)*
Updates include: laceration protection consideration, safety case requirement, safe distance from active participants, digital consent recording, and a separate weight limit for participants under 18.

### Section 5.6 – Pathway 2: Unlikely to cause serious harm on impact *(refinement)*
Updates include: impact test standard, simplified laceration protection, sustained overflight of moving vehicles >60 km/h, expanded 34J limit to emergency services third-parties, wind monitoring for PRS, and event operation clarification.

### Section 5.7 – Low altitude operations not over people *(new pathway)*
New OONP approval pathway for low altitude operations where overflight of people is not expected, if specified conditions are met.

### Section 5.8 – Parachute recovery system (PRS) *(new pathway)*
New pathway for drones using a PRS where maximum impact energy under PRS descent is ≤34 joules.

### Section 5.9 – Remove certain data collection requirements *(reduction)*
Remove duplicative or impractical data collection (drone details, minimum distance from people, collision consequences).

